Now, what benefit did this give us? Well for starters, now we have simplified the logic in our `input()` method. It may be a bit hard to read because there&#39;s 3 methods in one line, so that&#39;s a negative. But on the plus side, we are more loosely coupled. That helps us in a big way.

For example, your program has a minor formatting error. In the beginning, when you ask your user how many of each ingredient they want, your prompt comes out looking like this.

